cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.SOC, cs.DC 

The paper discusses the design of an overlay network constructed on top of a social network, which is primarily focused on network infrastructure and social network analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the clustering behavior of the graph structure and socializing patterns of members, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also addresses the construction of the overlay graph topology, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the deployment of applications such as group communication, content delivery, and data sharing, which is related to cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks).
